The paper deals with improving the Random Access Channel (RACH) procedure in the Long-Term Evolution (LTE) standard for machine-type traffic. This involves using machine learning techniques to detect collision multiplicity and improve the system load and transmission latency. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
